info","should_display_ad_info":false},"serialized_frtp_identifiers":null,"debug_info":null,"inform_treatment_for_community_notes":null,"message":{"text":"\ud83c\udf3f Honoring The Little Ones \ud83c\udf3f\n\nMany of you have seen our posts about the prayer garden we have started. \n\nAs my sweet friend Brenda Emmert, who has been a part of this journey with me, approaches her 50th birthday, we decided to do a little fundraiser to get started on the next phase of the garden! \n\nIt will be a place of healing and remembrance\u2014a Prayer Garden dedicated to families who have lost babies. In honor of Pregnancy and Infant Loss Awareness Month, we are inviting you to join us in this journey to bring comfort to those who grieve.\n\nThe garden has already begun with a boulder for each precious life lost by Brenda and her family, lovingly symbolizing every baby who remains forever in our hearts. Our hope is that this space will be a place of peace, healing, and connection with God.\n\nWould you consider making a donation to help with the next phase of this garden? Every gift, big or small, will be used to create a meaningful sanctuary for families to remember, pray, and find solace.\n\nTo contribute, please click here to donate! https:\/\/donate.stripe.com\/28o6qs9gH8Kh9La4gg  \n\nYour support in honoring these little lives would mean the world to The Emmert's and the families who will find comfort here.\n\nThank you for
